Name: Once the initial set out is complete the Administrator will determine the design appropriateness of the set out with regard to the actual site conditions
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual
Subsoil Drains constructed to appropriate dimensions, inspect trench prior to backfill
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual

Backfill materialshall be damp when placed in trench. Material shall be carefully placed in layers not exceeding 200mm loose thickness. Shall be compacted to achieve effective mechanical interlock between particles.
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual

Subsoil Drains shall be constructed in the locations and in accordance to the drawings. Subsoil Drains shall be installed to the grades specified in the drawings. Where the grades are not specified, the bottom of trenches shall be trimmed to provide not less that 0.5% longitudinal fall towards outlets for pipe type drains and not less that 1% longitudinal fall towards outlets for strip filter type drains.
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual
Cleanout and outlet pipes, Geotextiles, trench backfill, concrete for headwalls and surrounds, marker posts shall be as per specification
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual

Clean-outs shall be located at the heads of all subsoil drains and at subsequent spacings not exceeding 60m for Type B subsoil drains and 50m for Type D subsoil drains. Cleanouts shall be constructed in accordance with the details shown on Standard Drawings 1116.
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual
Marker posts installed where and when required as shown in the project drawings or standard drawings.
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual
Where directed by Administrator, drains shall be flushed until outlet water is clean and flows consistently
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Visual
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - As constructed drawings submitted to administrator
Acceptance Criteria and Frequency (Project Specific) - Survey
Supervisor/QA Verify that the Above has been Constructed according to Specification
